cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.PL, cs.AR

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a high-performance graph library for the GPU, which is a parallel computing architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of a data-centric abstraction for graph processing. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper uses optimization strategies to improve performance. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses a high-level programming model for graph processing. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper focuses on developing a graph library specifically for the GPU architecture.
